The article discusses the importance of unions in building the middle class and the potential for a clean energy transition to benefit both auto companies and unionized workers. The author emphasizes the need for good wages, benefits, and worker involvement in shaping the future of the industry. They call for a fair agreement between the Big Three auto companies and the United Auto Workers, with a focus on supporting the middle class and ensuring a smooth transition to clean energy. The author believes that the UAW should receive a contract that sustains the middle class as the industry moves towards new technologies.